This represents the first time the president has appeared in Parliament since the many calls for him to resign. CAPE TOWN - President Jacob Zuma is tabling the Presidency's budget vote in the National Assembly on Wednesday afternoon.He has been heckled by the DA during the address. The president was talking about &quot;a better life for all South Africans&quot; when DA MPs chimed in, saying achieving that would mean Zuma's resignation and relocation to Dubai.At the same time, Zuma has reiterated government's commitment to secure energy certainty for the country. The President has also celebrated strides made with the business sector to improve investor confidence in the country.WATCH: The Presidency budget vote